CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 20, 1954, pg. 11, reads: "Delta Officials - Shown at the midst of the program Sunday, March 14, at the YWCA where Delta Sigma Theta sorors held a workshop session, are three national officers and members of the planning committee. Left to right: Regional Director Janet Hamilton of Chicago, Miss Height, national president; Miss Nancy Lee, Grand Secretary of the sorority; Mary Baltimore, president of Alpha Epsilon Chapter; Soror Florence May, chairman of the area meeting, and Ardelle L. Douglas, secretary of Alpha Epsilon. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dorothy Height addressing officers and members of Delta Sigma Theta sorority, seated from left: Janet Hamilton, Nancy Lee, Mary Baltimore, Florence May, and Ardelle L. Douglas, gathered around table with candle, in YWCA
